---
import { ChevronDown, ExternalLink } from "lucide-astro";
import { website } from "../seo";
---

<!-- Data written directly in markup for maximum flexibility (no frontmatter) -->
<section
  class="pt-16 pb-16 lg:flex lg:items-start lg:gap-x-12"
  id="collaborate"
>
  <header
    class="mb-16 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-4 justify-between lg:flex-col lg:items-start"
  >
    <h2 class="text-4xl text-balance">
      Lets Build Together! Worst case scenario, we only have a great
      conversation.
    </h2>

    <a
      href={`mailto:${website.email}`}
      class="px-0 flex gap-x-1 mt-4 text-sm hover:underline underline-offset-2 text-nowrap text-blue-600"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      {`Write me an email`}
      <ExternalLink class="size-4 stroke-current" />
    </a>
  </header>

  <div id="collaboration-faq" class="grow accordion-container lg:max-w-md">
    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          How do I get in touch?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Send a message introducing yourself and what I can help you with via
          email or my <a href="#summary" class="underline">socials</a>. We'll
          take it from there. I'll respond within 24-48 hours.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          What services do you offer?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          I work on web apps, dashboards, internal tools, automation and
          platform infrastructure, most of the time. If you have a process
          that’s manual, inefficient, or non-existent; I can design and build
          the software and systems to handle it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          Do you only build websites and frontend?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          No. I build products, not just pages. I work on anything from landing
          pages to full platforms with authentication, databases, payments,
          messaging or real-time features. If it runs in the browser or on a
          server, I can make it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          How do projects with you usually work?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Tell me what you're trying to build, fix or improve. If I find myself
          a good fit, we’ll talk. If not, I’ll point you in the right direction.
          Depending on the project, I’ll either work fast in isolation or
          closely with you in short feedback loops.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          What technologies do you specialize in?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Modern JavaScript (Next/Astro, Node/Nest, ORMs & Tailwind) for most
          builds. Also Headless Systems (Firebase, Ghost) and IDE AI! I’m
          flexible; tech is a tool, not a religion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          I'm not technical. Is that a problem?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Nope. Your job is to explain the goal in plain everyday (or business)
          language. My job is to translate it into a product: logic, features,
          and delivery. My degree backed background in Project Management also
          makes this easier for me.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #collaboration-faq .ac-container,
  #collaboration-faq .ac,
  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger {
    background: transparent;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger {
    border: none;
    display: flex;
    flex: 1;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    text-align: start;
    cursor: pointer;
    @apply text-foreground text-base font-medium sm:text-lg;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger:focus,
  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger:hover {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger::after {
    content: "";
    display: none;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-content {
    overflow: hidden;
    animation-duration: 0.2s;
    animation-timing-function: ease-out;
    animation-fill-mode: forwards;
    padding-inline: 0px;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel {
    @apply font-sans !text-sm;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel > *:first-child {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel > *:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-content[data-state="open"] {
    animation-name: accordion-down;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac {
    @apply border-x-transparent border-t-transparent border-b border-b-muted-foreground/15;
  }
</style>

<script>
  import Accordion from "accordion-js";
  import "accordion-js/dist/accordion.min.css";

  new Accordion("#collaboration-faq", {
    duration: 300,
    showMultiple: false,
    collapse: true,
    openOnInit: [0],
  });
</script>
